This is about **Bulma**.

This is a feature request, based on unexpected behaviour in `.button.is-primary:hover`.

### Overview of the problem

This is about the Bulma **CSS framework**
I'm using Bulma **version 0.8.0**
My **browser** is **Firefox 71.0b9, Fedora 30**

I am rather sure this issue is **not a duplicate**, but could be related to #1753 and #1944.


### Description

With the new `$color-light` and `$color-dark` variables and maps introduced, I expected these colors to also be applied to the `:hover`/`.is-hovered` states of `.button.is-primary`.
Unfortunately, in the [`button.sass` element](https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/d4c7731792e1a62d89d784544f7a50d7a6cfcd6d/sass/elements/button.sass#L126) the background-color value is set to `darken($color, 2.5%)` instead.

I assume this is used in order to derive appropiate colors for `:hover` and `:focus` states.
For my use case it'd be highly beneficial to provide those values myself in order to match these states with our internal Design style guide requirements, but also for supporting a dark scheme (where the hover state would be more emphasised by a lighter shade instead of a darker one).

Hence, I'd like to request a customisable way to introduce custom `hover`, `focus` and `active` colors (without the need of a `custom.css` file that overrides only those states).
Possible options for this could be to introduce...
1. additional variables `$color-<scheme>-bis` and `$color-<scheme>-ter` (e.g. `$primary-light-ter` or `$info-dark-bis`) that would be re-used for `focus`/`hover`/`active` states.
2. additional variables `$color-<state>` (e.g. `$primary-focus`, `$info-active`, `$success-hover`) that would be specifically applied to those states
3. additional variables `$hover-shading`, `$focus-shading` and `$active-shading` which be used for applying the percentage in `darken()` and `lighten()` calls
4. new methods `getHoverColor($color)`, `getFocusColor($color)` and `getActiveColor($color)` which would be using the existing logic, but could be overwritten manually"


### Steps to Reproduce

(Reproducable with the [minimal customised `node-sass` setup](https://bulma.io/documentation/customize/with-node-sass/))

1. In your `mystyles.scss`, create a custom color map, e.g.
```scss
// Import default variables
@import "../node_modules/bulma/sass/utilities/initial-variables.sass";

// In this example, the color map for `.is-primary` will be replaced
$custom-colors: ("primary": ($red, $white, $yellow, $green));

// Import other Bulma code including derived-variables.sass
// to merge the $custom-colors map to the regular $colors map
@import "../node_modules/bulma/sass/utilities/_all.sass";
@import "../node_modules/bulma/sass/base/_all.sass";
@import "../node_modules/bulma/sass/elements/button.sass";
```
2. Create a [`mypage.html` file according to the documentation](https://github.com/jgthms/bulma/blob/d4c7731792e1a62d89d784544f7a50d7a6cfcd6d/docs/_includes/snippets/mypage.html) and make sure it contains a primary button:
```html
<a class="button is-primary">Primary</a>
```


### Expected behavior

When hovering, the `Primary` button, I expect the `background-color` to change from `$red` to `$green`, as this is the supposed color for `$primary-dark` in the `$custom-colors` map (which is merged into the `$colors` map).


### Actual behavior

When hovering, the background color changes to a 2.5% darker shade of `$red`. Currently, it's not possible to change this colour via SASS/CSS variables.


I'd also like take the opportunity to thank you very much for your work on Bulma! :)

Unless I'm confused...

Media query for is-hidden-tablet is wrong (current master):

```
@media screen and (min-width: 769px), print {
  .is-hidden-tablet {
    display: none !important;
  }
}
```

Should read:

```
@media screen and (max-width: 1023px), print {
    .is-hidden-tablet {
        display: none !important;
    }
}
```
